<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

    {% set title = "" %}
    {%include "header"%}

    <style>
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed {
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
          box-sizing: border-box;
          min-width: 0;
          max-width: 100%;
          vertical-align: bottom;
          background-clip: padding-box;
          scrollbar-color: rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.1) rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.5);
          display: grid;
          grid-auto-flow: column;
          gap: 0.75rem;
          grid-template-columns: 1fr;
          grid-auto-columns: max-content;
          align-items: center;
          background-color: #ad765b; /* Form background color */
          border-radius: 0.25rem;
          box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); /* Box shadow */
          border: none; /* No border */
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-button {
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
          box-sizing: border-box;
          min-width: 0;
          max-width: 100%;
          vertical-align: bottom;
          background-clip: padding-box;
          scrollbar-color: rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.1) rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.5);
          background: transparent;
          font-size: 1rem;
          line-height: 1.5;
          padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
          color: #f6f3ee; /* Text color */
          border-radius: 0.25rem;
          font-family: 'Mabry Pro', 'Avenir', 'Montserrat', 'Corbel', 'URW Gothic', 'source-sans-pro', sans-serif;
          display: inline-flex;
          align-items: center;
          justify-content: center;
          gap: 0.5rem;
          cursor: pointer;
          text-decoration: none;
          transition-timing-function: ease-out;
          transition-duration: 0.14s;
          transition-property: all;
          background-color: #ad765b;
          box-shadow: 0 4px 8px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.1); /* Box shadow */
          border: none; /* No border */
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-button:hover {
          transform: translate(-0.25rem, -0.25rem);
          box-shadow: 0.25rem 0.25rem 0rem rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.5);
          background-color: #f690e8;
          color: #f6f3ee;
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-input {
          margin: 0;
          padding: 0;
          box-sizing: border-box;
          min-width: 0;
          max-width: 100%;
          vertical-align: bottom;
          background-clip: padding-box;
          scrollbar-color: rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.1) rgba(246, 243, 238, 0.5);
          font-family: 'Mabry Pro', 'Avenir', 'Montserrat', 'Corbel', 'URW Gothic', 'source-sans-pro', sans-serif;
          padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
          font-size: 1rem;
          font-weight: bold; /* Bold text */
          line-height: 1.5;
          border-radius: 0.25rem;
          display: block;
          width: 100%;
          background-color: #ad765b;
          color: #f6f3ee; /* Text color */
          border: none; /* No border */
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-input:disabled {
          cursor: not-allowed;
          opacity: 0.3;
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-input::placeholder {
          color: #f6f3ee; /* Placeholder text color */
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-input:focus-within {
          outline: 0.125rem solid #f690e8;
        }
      
        #gumroad-follow-form-embed-input:read-only {
          background-color: #242423;
        }
      </style>

    <body>
        <header>
            <h1>MoKa Reads</h1>
            <button class="w3-button w3-xlarge nav mobile-show"
                onclick="w3_open()">â˜°</button>
        </header>
        {% include "nav" %}

        <div class="container w3-mobile">
            <!-- Open-Source Education Section -->
            <section class="open-source-section w3-mobile">
                <h2>Open-Source Education and Programming</h2>
                <p>
                    At MoKa Reads, we are passionate about open-source
                    education, especially in the realm of programming.
                    Embracing open-source principles in programming education
                    enables a collaborative learning environment
                    where aspiring developers and seasoned coders alike can
                    learn from, contribute to, and improve each
                    other's work.
                </p>
                <p>
                    By supporting open-source programming projects, we believe
                    in empowering educators and learners to
                    explore new technologies, exchange ideas, and build
                    real-world projects together. As a result, our
                    platform fosters innovation, creativity, and a strong sense
                    of community within the programming
                    education landscape.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Additionally, our commitment to open-source extends to our
                    publications. By making educational resources
                    open and accessible, we aim to enrich the programming
                    community with high-quality content while
                    providing a platform for aspiring authors to share their
                    knowledge and expertise.
                </p>
                <div class="hidden">
                    <h3>Benefits of Open-Source Education in Programming:</h3>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Enhanced collaboration and knowledge sharing among
                            programmers.</li>
                        <li>Opportunities to learn from real-world,
                            industry-standard projects.</li>
                        <li>Exposure to diverse perspectives and problem-solving
                            approaches.</li>
                        <li>Community-driven support and feedback for continuous
                            improvement.</li>
                        <li>Empowerment to create and publish educational
                            content for the community.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </section>

            <form
                class="input-with-button"
                action="https://app.gumroad.com/follow_from_embed_form"
                method="post" id="gumroad-follow-form-embed"><input
                    type="hidden" name="seller_id"
                    value="6843762831327" />
                <input
                    id="gumroad-follow-form-embed-input" type="email"
                    placeholder="Your email address" name="email"
                    value /><button id="gumroad-follow-form-embed-button"
                    class="primary" type="submit">Follow</button></form>

            <section class="supported-languages-section w3-mobile">
                <h2>Languages in Focus</h2>
                <div class="supported-languages-container w3-mobile">

                    <div class="language-card">
                        <a href="https://www.rust-lang.org/">
                            <i class="language-icon devicon-rust-plain"></i>
                            <div class="language-name">Rust</div>
                            <div class="language-description">
                                Rust is a modern systems programming language
                                that uniquely combines speed, control, and
                                safety. It is designed to empower developers to
                                write efficient and reliable code while
                                providing them with the flexibility and
                                low-level control needed to build complex
                                systems. Rust's safety features, such as its
                                ownership model and strict compile-time checks,
                                make it a popular choice for building safe and
                                reliable high-performance software.
                            </div>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="language-card">
                        <a href="https://en.cppreference.com/w/">
                            <i class="language-icon devicon-c-plain"></i>
                            <i
                                class="language-icon devicon-cplusplus-plain"></i>
                            <div class="language-name">C/C++</div>
                            <div class="language-description">
                                C and C++ are two dynamic programming languages.
                                C is a great option for system programming and
                                embedded systems as it is robust and efficient.
                                On the other hand, C++ is a modern extension of
                                C that incorporates object-oriented features,
                                making it perfect for contemporary software
                                development. Both languages are excellent at
                                creating efficient and robust solutions for
                                system-level tasks, embedded systems, and
                                high-performance applications. They bridge the
                                gap between traditional and modern programming
                                paradigms.
                            </div>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                    <div class="language-card">
                        <a href="https://ziglang.org/">
                            <i class="language-icon devicon-zig-original"></i>
                            <div class="language-name">Zig</div>
                            <div class="language-description">
                                Zig is a cutting-edge programming language that
                                boasts an effortless and intuitive approach to
                                coding. It is designed to prioritize
                                performance, safety, and readability, making it
                                an excellent choice for systems and game
                                development. With Zig, you can enjoy a seamless
                                and streamlined programming experience that
                                allows you to build complex and robust
                                applications easily. Its user-friendly interface
                                and advanced features make Zig a popular choice
                                among developers who value efficiency and
                                reliability.
                            </div>
                        </a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>
        </div>

        {% include "footer" %}
    </body>

</html>